Text.Value: Say nothing.
Then you two are enemies - not friends.
I remember you, but you're different... very different. I used to call you something else, didn't I?
Ah... a pity. Perhaps we can talk some more later, if you wish.
Still, we need to be careful... The Mother Superior holds a tight grip on this place. But perhaps I can help you in the meanwhile.
Indeed. There must be all sorts of things you could tell me.
It seems the whispers were right on that last part, my lady. At some point she confused her ambitions for the Nightsinger's will.
They said the hunt for the artefact was a suicide mission - I feared I wouldn't see you again. Some even thought it was the Mother Superior's plan alone, and not what Lady Shar wanted...
I couldn't keep going like that. But seeing how you fought on, I realised that I didn't have to. From then on, I was Nocturne. It wasn't easy... but everything started to make sense. I could breathe.
Only if you wish us to be. You helped me be true to myself - I will not begrudge you for discovering yourself... even if it displeases Lady Shar.
Shadowheart... I wasn't sure if I'd ever lay eyes on you again. It's me, Nocturne. Do you remember?
I expect you'll have catching-up to do.
You command this place now, Shadowheart. What happens is your choice.
We... we trained together. We used to be close.
They were attacking who you were. I never found it funny, but wasn't quite sure why. Eventually I realised it was because I wasn't happy with who I was.
Not if Shadowheart doesn't wish for it. She helped me be true to myself - I will not begrudge her for doing the same... even if it displeases Lady Shar.
It seems the whispers were right, on that last part. At some point she confused her ambitions for the Nightsinger's will.
Her followers... and my friends, in at least some cases. I was so focused on getting here, on finishing this, I forgot about the life I had here.
I'll need to be careful... The Mother Superior holds a tight grip on this place. But perhaps I can help you in the meanwhile.
Viconia is defeated. It's up to you what happens to her followers.
You can reminisce after you've dealt with Viconia, Shadowheart.
I wish... to know more. There must be all sort of things you can tell me. Little things from my past, lost to Lady Shar's embrace.
Come see me when you have time - I work as quartermaster now. I can sell you some things... and we can catch up.
You don't need Shar.
You don't, perhaps. Not everyone is as brave.
There are... but you need to finish what you came here for. Everyone knows you've been blessed, that you're coming for the Mother Superior. I won't stand in your way.
Ah... a pity. Perhaps we can talk some more later. That is, if you're not about to turn on me... It seems you no longer walk in the Dark Lady's shadow.
I don't remember you.
*You recall the memory Shadowheart recovered by eating the noblestalk - this must be the person she remembered.*
Shar condemned me. By her decree, you and I are enemies.
That's... good enough for me. I'm not sure what I expected coming back to this place - certainly not a friend.
I've been trying to return here as long as I can remember... which admittedly doesn't amount to much.
Be careful... Whatever she has planned, I don't think she'll shed any tears if you are a casualty along the way.
It's a beautiful name. Suits you well.
But now it seems you've turned on both the Mother Superior and Lady Shar...
Remind me.

EditorData.NodeContext: A touch suspicious - greeted warmly by someone she doesn't remember.

Text.Value: You're right. I need to finish this.
There must be all sorts you can tell me. Things I can't even remember.
Not if Shadowheart doesn't wish for it. She may not remember, but we shared a lot together once. Good times, hard times... I will not turn on her. Even if it angers Lady Shar.
I'm glad to see you're all right.
Indeed. There must be all sorts of things you could tell me.
Only if you wish us to be. You may not remember, but we shared a lot together once. Good times, hard times... I will not turn on you. Even if it angers Lady Shar.
Come see me when you have time - I work as quartermaster now. I can sell you some things... and we can catch up.
If you wish it of me... of course, my lady. I work as the quartermaster. Come see me whenever you wish.
Ah... a pity. Perhaps we can talk some more later. That is, if you wish, my lady.
There are... but with the Mother Superior gone, I don't know if I can stay here to reminisce. Perhaps there's another enclave out there for me.
I didn't see her amongst your supporters fighting Viconia. You shouldn't trust her.
Still, we need to be careful... The Mother Superior holds a tight grip on this place. But perhaps I can help you in the meanwhile.
Thank you. Picked it myself. But enough of that - I can't believe you're back.

EditorData.NodeContext: Lighthearted. Flyby reference to their pronouns on 'I'm them'.

Text.Value: I'll leave come tomorrow. Come see me before then - I was working as quartermaster. I can sell you some things to aid you... and we can catch up.
Some even thought it was the Mother Superior's plan alone, and not Lady Shar's intent...
You did - but that's not who I am now. I remember the other initiates used to tease you about your name - the one you chose to honour Lady Shar.
There are... but you need to finish what you came here for. If half of the rumours about what was done to you are true... well, I won't stand in your way.
She's one of them. You can't trust her.
Perhaps you're right... but I trusted her once. That has to count for something.
But no matter - you rule us now. What comes next?

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Shadowheart gives a questioning glance to the player after Nightshade speaks ('what DOES come next?')

Text.Value: Ah... a pity. Perhaps we can talk some more later, if you wish.
They... they whispered it was a suicide mission, this search for the artefact you were sent on.

Synopsis: Shadowheart meets with her old friend once again. Talking about the past and discussing what the future is going to look like.
